<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="1361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1361">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/179.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-25">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In compliance with a request from the Spanish Embassy, renew your
                                efforts to have an investigation of the killing of the Gonzalez
                                brothers. Impress with all earnestness upon appropriate authorities
                                the extreme importance of having this action taken immediately.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>